Lefthook is a Git hooks manager.
Example: Run your linters on pre-commit hook and forget about the routine.
# lefthook.yml

pre-commit:
  parallel: true
  jobs:
    - run: yarn run stylelint --fix {staged_files}
      glob: &quot;*.css&quot;
      stage_fixed: true

    - run: yarn run eslint --fix &quot;{staged_files}&quot;
      glob:
        - &quot;*.ts&quot;
        - &quot;*.js&quot;
        - &quot;*.tsx&quot;
        - &quot;*.jsx&quot;
      stage_fixed: true
